H3.text: Which car manufacturer produces a model called the RAV4. トヨタ

A4.text: The Toyota RAV4 is a compact crossover SUV produced by the Japanese automobile manufacturer Toyota.

A5.text: The RAV4 is one of the best-selling SUVs of all time, having sold over 10 million units by February 2020.

A6.text: A second plug-in hybrid model, the Toyota RAV4 PHV (RAV4 Prime in the US) was unveiled in December 2019. Sales started in mid-2020.

A7.text: A second generation of the RAV4 EV was developed in 2010 as part of a deal with Tesla. The production version was unveiled in August 2012, using battery pack, electronics and powertrain components from Tesla.
